Dhoti Lota Aur Chowpatty is a 1975 Bollywood film directed by Mohan Choti and noted for its large cast and guest appearances.

An assortment of characters living near Juhu, Chowpatty, meet, share comic, romantic, and fight scenes. This movie is remembered for the reverse casting as main heros such as Dharam and Sanjeev have wee bit roles, whereas the wee bit character roles usally played by Mohan Choti, and Farida Jalal, are the main characters. 

